sections.heading: to 61-19A-34 - Repealed.
sections.text:
Repeals.— Laws 1993, ch. 171, § 28 repealed former 61-19A-1 to 61-19A-25 NMSA 1978, as enacted by Laws 1979, ch. 382, §§ 1 to 25 and amended by Laws 1982, ch. 106, §§ 1 to 4, Laws 1984, ch. 44, § 1, and Laws 1989, ch. 110, §§ 1 to 4, regulating cosmetology, effective June 18, 1993. For present comparable provisions,seeChapter 61, Article 17A NMSA 1978.

Laws 1989, ch. 110, § 7 repeals former 61-19A-26 NMSA 1978, as enacted by Laws 1979, ch. 382, § 26, relating to reissue of authority after revocation, effective June 26, 1989.

Laws 1993, ch. 171, § 28 repealed former 61-19A-27 to 61-19A-34 NMSA 1978, as enacted by Laws 1979, ch. 382, §§ 27 to 34, and amended by Laws 1989, ch. 110, §§ 5 and 6, concerning exemptions; prohibited acts; sanitary rules; investigations; entry and inspection; remedies; confidentiality; and repeal of the article, effective June 18, 1993. For present comparable provisions,seeChapter 61, Article 17A NMSA 1978.
